OL,3,CDouglas Ross to quit as Scottish Tory
OL,4,Cleader after general election
OL,6,FFormer UK government minister David
OL,7,FDuguid had wanted to fight the seat,
OL,8,Fbut the Scottish Conservative Party
OL,9,Fmanagement board ruled ill health
OL,10,Fmeant he should not stand, with Mr
OL,11,FRoss confirming last week that he
OL,12,Fwould put himself forward for the
OL,13,Fconstituency.
OL,15,FIt comes after Mr Ross, who is also an
OL,16,FMSP, had previously vowed he would
OL,17,Fstep down from Westminster to focus on
OL,18,FHolyrood and his role as party leader.
